The Borno Coalition for Justice (BCJ) has accused politicians and some aides to the state governor, Professor Babagana Zulum, of an attempt to embarrass President Muhammadu Buhari during his visit to Maiduguri on Wednesday. The coalition made this known yesterday at a press conference to address the “despicable plot at embarrassing President Buhari by aides of the governor.” Speaking on behalf of the Borno Coalition, Convener, Mohammed Ali, described the attempt as “cowardly and insensitive”. As indigenes of Borno, the group recounts that President Buhari enjoys demigod status in the state owing to his giant strides which dates back to his military days adding that it is impossible for the same people to turn their backs on him. The coalition said the handwriting of some disgruntled politicians in the state was all over the show of shame. The Borno Coalition for Justice, therefore, advised Governor Zulum to call his aides and other politicians in the state to order and go a step further by tendering an unreserved apology to the President. The group, told President Buhari not to be perturbed and continue his drastic approach to insecurity by declaring a state of emergency on the state. ‘’The Borno Coalition for Justice is indeed appalled by the display of hypocrisy by the government of Borno State for allowing street urchins under the sponsorship of aides and advisers of the Governor throw tantrums at the convoy of President Muhammadu Buhari. ‘’This is indeed unsolicited and an indication that the government of Borno State is not appreciative of the numerous sacrifices President Muhammadu Buhari has made for the people of Borno State in ensuring that the Boko Haram insurgency comes to an end. ‘’We wish to state that this display is cowardly and insensitive. It is indeed a continuation of the contempt which the Governor of Borno State and his immediate predecessor have for President Muhammadu Buhari,’’ the group said.